      "question": "Find the area of a sector of a circle with radius $6 \\text{ cm}$ if the angle of the sector is $60^\\circ$. (Use $\\pi = 3.14$)",
      "answer": "18.84 \\text{ cm}^2",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the formula for the area of a sector: $A = \\frac{\\theta}{360^\\circ} \\times \\pi r^2$.",
          "Substitute the given values $r=6$ and $\\theta=60$ into the formula and calculate."
        ],
        "derivation": "A = \\frac{60}{360} \\times 3.14 \\times 6^2 = \\frac{1}{6} \\times 3.14 \\times 36 = 3.14 \\times 6 = 18.84 \\text{ cm}^2"
